DECISION: Rex Flynn is established as a DRAFT influencer character in Apex Chronicles. His platform is called "Exposed," operating across TikTok and YouTube in two distinct voice registers. Rex is male, 20s, loud and boisterous — an anti-hero with no fixed ideological position who chases clickbait and emotional response exclusively, capable of praising or burying the hero depending on what's performing. Mechanically, he is one of three feedback channels. His primary reward pillar is run modifier unlocks, framed as arbitrary public demands Rex makes of the hero, justified with unhinged logic optimized for engagement. His secondary reward is name emergence options (editorial, chaotic, meme-driven, viral-optimized). TikTok register is punchy and clipped; YouTube register is unhinged and sprawling.

DATE: May 3, 2026

WHY: Rex Flynn's platform-chasing nature makes him a more contemporary and mechanically interesting antagonist than an institutional critic. Having no fixed position means modifier challenges feel unpredictable and genuinely funny. The dual platform format gives writers two distinct voice registers to work with.

